Razorpay KYC won't approve a merchant without these pages live on the
public domain. Adding five pages all wired to a shared <LegalLayout/>:

- /privacy        DPDP Act 2023 compliant. Lists data collected,
                  purpose, retention, user rights, grievance officer
                  (Karthikeya, privacy@jovio.in). Calls out India-only
                  data residency (Mumbai), AES-256 encryption at rest,
                  72-hour breach notification commitment.
- /terms          Acceptable use (no TRAI violations, no scraping),
                  billing & cancellation, third-party service deps
                  (Sarvam/Gemini/LiveKit/Razorpay/Wati/Exotel),
                  Hyderabad jurisdiction, limited liability cap.
- /refund-policy  14-day trial (no card), monthly subs non-refundable
                  except 7-day window on first paid charge + service
                  outage credits, annual subs 14-day refund window.
                  Razorpay refund timeline (UPI 5-7d, card 7-14d).
- /contact        Topic-tagged email routes (sales/support/billing/
                  privacy/legal/security), business hours, registered
                  office (Hyderabad, full address shared under NDA).
- /pricing        Standalone pricing page with plan details, overage
                  rates (Rs3/min), add-ons, volume-discount contact.

Shared LegalLayout component handles the sticky-nav header + footer
+ typography (h2/h3/p/ul/a styles via scoped <style>).

These are SUBSTANTIVE drafts based on India SaaS norms but ARE NOT
A SUBSTITUTE FOR LEGAL REVIEW. Have a lawyer (or NCLAT-registered
company secretary) verify before public launch.
