Three tiered limiters via express-rate-limit:
- tightLimiter   30 req / 15 min — for auth-sensitive paths (future use)
- webhookLimiter 60 req / minute — burst-cap on /webhooks/*. Razorpay
                                   and Exotel legitimately burst, but
                                   this prevents billing surprises if
                                   a malformed retry loop hits us.
- apiLimiter    300 req / 15 min — generic protection on /api/*

Also set 'trust proxy' to 1 — Railway/Vercel sit one hop in front of
the api server. Without this, rate-limit keys on the edge IP and one
attacker can DoS every customer. With it, req.ip is the real client.

Added express-rate-limit@^7.4.1 + @types/express@^5 to package.json.
