MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Single-EC2 Ubuntu 24 in ap-south-1 with Nginx + systemd + CloudWatch.
No code changes — application is already proxy-aware (trust proxy: 1)
so it works behind Nginx today and can move behind ALB later with
zero code changes.

Files:

  infra/aws/cloudwatch-agent.json
    CloudWatch Agent config covering:
    - CPU / mem / disk / swap / netstat metrics (1-min interval,
      Jovio/EC2 namespace, InstanceId + InstanceType dimensions)
    - Log group ingestion for both apps + Nginx access/error logs
      with 14-30 day retention

  infra/aws/setup-cloudwatch.sh
    Downloads + installs the official CW agent .deb for Ubuntu 24,
    applies the config, enables on boot. Requires the EC2 to have
    the CloudWatchAgentServerPolicy managed policy attached via
    an IAM role.

  infra/systemd/jovio-pipeline.service
  infra/systemd/jovio-api.service
    Drop-in replacement for the existing Supervisor setup. Loads
    secrets from /etc/jovio/*.env (mode 0640, root:ubuntu) so they
    never live in the repo. Hardening: NoNewPrivileges, PrivateTmp,
    ProtectSystem=full, memory caps. Restart policy: always, 10s
    delay, 5 restarts in 60s before backing off.

  infra/nginx/jovio.conf
    Reverse proxy: api.jovio.in -> 127.0.0.1:4000,
                   pipeline.jovio.in -> 127.0.0.1:8000.
    /health + /ready bypassed from access logs to keep them clean
    under Route 53 health-check pressure. WebSocket upgrade headers
    on pipeline. for LiveKit signalling. 10-min read/send timeouts
    on pipeline. for long calls.

  infra/aws/AWS_DEPLOYMENT.md
    End-to-end guide: EC2 launch, IAM role, env file setup,
    secret generation commands, systemd migration from supervisor,
    Nginx + certbot, CloudWatch agent, Route 53 health checks,
    operations runbook (deploy / rollback / log tailing), cost
    estimate (~Rs 2,160/month for t3.small), security checklist,
    when to migrate to ALB.

  voice-pipeline/setup_ec2_ubuntu24.sh
    Appended next-steps block pointing at the new infra files.
